Pour the @water{300%ml} into a #saucepan{} and bring to the boil. When boiling, add @salt{0.25%tsp}, stir in the @Jasmine Rice{150%g}, lower the heat to medium and pop a #lid{} on the pan. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Trim and thinly slice the @Radishes{100%g}(trimmed and thinly sliced). Trim the @Cucumber{½}(halved lengthways) then halve lengthways. Thinly slice widthways. Zest and halve the @Lime{½}(zested and halved). Drain the @Firm Tofu{280%g}, pat it dry and chop into 2cm pieces.

Heat large #frying pan{} over medium heat (no oil!) Once hot, add the @Sesame Seeds{15%g} and cook, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted, ~{1-2%minutes}. Pop half the sesame seeds a #medium bowl{} and set aside. Pop the remaining half into a #small bowl{} and set aside. (Don't wash up the frying pan). In another small bowl mix together the @Rice Vinegar{15%ml} and @Sugar{½%tbsp} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add the sliced radishes, mix together well and set aside.

> The Thai Style Spice Mix is quite spicy - use according to your preference.

Pop the @Cornflour{20%g} and @Thai Style Spice Mix{½%tsp} into a medium bowl. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Mix together well. Add the tofu and toss to coat evenly. Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in the pan you used earlier on medium high heat. Once hot add the tofu and fry until golden brown and crispy all over, turning regularly, ~{5-6%minutes}. Transfer to a #plate{} lined with #kitchen roll{} and allow the pan to cool slightly but don't wash it, we will use it for the teriyaki glaze.

Meanwhile, pop the sliced cucumber into the medium bowl with the sesame seeds. Squeeze in the lime juice, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and toss to coat. Once the rice is ready, wipe out the frying pan if you need to then add the @Teriyaki Sauce{75%ml}. Bring to the boil, add the tofu and stir until everything is evenly coated and the tofu is piping hot.

> Add a splash of water if the sauce has evaporated too much.

Carefully fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and stir through the lime zest. Divide the rice between #bowls{}, top with the teriyaki tofu and its sauce on one side then add the cucumber salad and pickled radish on the other side. Scatter over the remaining sesame seeds. Enjoy!